<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 6:05PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN HUNTINGDON AND
NORTHEASTERN FRANKLIN COUNTIES THROUGH 645 PM EDT...
At 604 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from McConnellsburg to Shirleysburg. Movement was
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rockhill Furnace, Upper Strasburg, Roxbury, Willow Hill, Doylesburg,
Fannettsburg, Three Springs, Orbisonia, Saltillo, Shirleysburg and
Shade Gap.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
